ss.\n  - Persists two `BatchAuthor` entities through Hibernate Reactive.\n  - Loads one entity into the session persistence context, then performs unordered multi-load with session checking enabled so the managed/non-managed split reaches `Array.newInstance(...)`.\n\n- `tests/src/org.hibernate.reactive/hibernate-reactive-core/2.0.7.Final/src/test/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml`\n  - Added `mysql-standard-multiload` persistence unit for the dedicated test.\n\nPer instruction, I did not run compilation or tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_08478571cc423ec1016a15e8dafb3881a3ac112493b244a9b5\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 844, "output": 970, "cacheRead": 52736, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 54550, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779820745857, "responseId": "resp_08478571cc423ec1016a15e8ca904481a3a335857bae332940"}}
