[assistant-event] text_start
[assistant] Fixed the reported failures with these changes:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `ReactiveMultiIdEntityLoaderStandardTest`
[assistant]   - Now creates and uses `ReactiveSessionImpl` from Hibernate Reactive’s Vert.x context via `Implementor#getContext().execute(...)`.
[assistant]   - Avoids constructing the reactive session on the JUnit timeout thread, which caused:
[assistant]     ```text
[assistant]     HR000068: This method should exclusively be invoked from a Vert.x EventLoop thread
[assistant]     ```
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `persistence.xml`
[assistant]   - Added the missing `postgres-entity-array-param-batch` persistence unit used by the existing array-param tests.
[assistant]   - Kept the dedicated `mysql-standard-multiload` persistence unit for the new active-class test.
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `build.gradle`
[assistant]   - Added:
[assistant]     ```groovy
[assistant]     testImplementation 'io.vertx:vertx-pg-client:4.5.0'
[assistant]     ```
[assistant]   - This supports the PostgreSQL reactive persistence unit used by the existing PostgreSQL-oriented tests.
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not rerun the Gradle test command, per workflow instruction.
[assistant-event] text_end
